09/12/2004
MOSTAR, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During a visit to Mostar on Wednesday (8 December), Serbian President Boris Tadic called for ethnic reconciliation and mutual forgiveness. 
Following talks with Federation of BiH President Niko Lozancic and Mostar officials, Tadic said Serbs and Bosnia's should apologise to each other for the past and focus on establishing normal relations.
In other news, the Serbia-Montenegro Parliament is expected to discuss and vote Thursday on a draft resolution regarding the federal union's integration into the EU. 
The adoption of such a resolution is a formal condition for all countries aspiring to membership. 
(Mezzanine novice, Beta, Tan jug - 09/12/04; Pincom.info, Beta, B92 - 08/12/04)
